reviewText: Image quality is murky throughout. And the content is silly,sexually hung-up sixties piffle. Don't bother.

Want to buy a DVD transfered from a guy videotaping from his movie seat ? Or a product that makes a VHS version look great side by side ? Well folks, this is the ticket for you. The print is awful. The film itself is not great, but it's a real 60's period piece, all those great actors in a low budget, poorly lit film with no skin, just mucho tease. Skip it.
